name: Glover Alston Center (Whitman College)
directions: 2 accessible bathrooms on the first floor, 1 non-accessible bathroom on the second floor
comment: Open only to people with valid Whitman IDs.  The building is currently open 10AM to 10PM Monday through Friday and 11AM to 8PM Saturday and Sunday.

name: Lowes Home Improvement
directions: Right next to the womens and mens bathrooms, near the self-check lanes
comment: I used to work at Lowes and this was my favorite place in the whole store.

name: University of Florida - Peabody Hall
directions: 202 Peabody Hall. 2nd floor of building, to the left of the information desk, near Multicultural and Diversity Affairs department - it\\\\\\\\\\\\\\'s a family restroom
comment: Building houses the LGBT Affairs Office and is open from 8-5, friendly staff...we are working on posting all the safe bathrooms we can find!

name: University of Florida - Carleton Auditorium
directions: front of the room to the left of the stage area
comment: Lecture hall for large classes so its just a huge room. Open from 9-5 but classes are usually inside (if you can hit the 15 minute period between classes you'll have no problem). Not the best condition, but it's there if needed!

name: University of Florida - Ustler Hall
street: E W Dr near Fletcher Dr
directions: 2 single stall locking restrooms labeled \'women\' on the 1st floor, 2 gender neutral restrooms each on the 2nd & 3rd floors. For the gender neutral bathrooms they are in the back left corner of the large room where PSU meets, same place on the third floor
comment: The building houses UF\'s Center for Women\'s Studies & Gender Research with really friendly staff and is usually open from 9-5. Classes are sometimes in session, so be quiet, but you can easily get in and out with no issues. Only downside is there is no available parking around the building :(

name: Twist Yarn Shop
directions: Ask an employee for directions to the restroom--it's gender-free and lockable, located in the back of the store.  The owner is transfriendly; the business is small, locally owned, and amazing.  So browse and buy, if you can!
comment: Tues., Wed., Fri. 10-5:30Thu., Sat. 10-8:00Stitch and Bitch meets 6-8 on Thursday and Saturday, is a pretty queer-friendly crowd.

name: Donut Whole
directions: Both restrooms are located in the hallway connecting the front and back halves of the restaurant.
comment: The Donut Whole has great hours--the lobby is open 6 a.m. to midnight, 7 days a week.  Restrooms are gendered, but single-stall and out of public view.  It's a very queer-friendly space, as are most of its customers.  And the donuts and coffee are terrific, so buy some on the way out!

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: In the back, there's a small hallway to the right. It's the first door on the left.
comment: It says \"no public restrooms\" on the door, but I've been allowed to use it.  Buying something and asking permission (or sneaking in when it's busy) might be a good idea.

name: fresenius dialysis centers
directions: ground floor
comment: most 6:am  til 3:pm

name: Viet-Thai Restaurant
directions: Two gendered single-seaters in back right of restaurant.
comment: It's a restaurant, so you've gotta buy something.  There's good Vietnamese and Thai food, if you're hungry!

name: East Carson Street
directions: Near parking area
comment: Must pay to pee. Open 24 hours. 20 minute maximum.

name: Identity Youth Center
comment: Only for youth 14-20. Very transgender friendly space.

name: The Cube
directions: In the back
comment: It's an LGBTQ community center - feel free to come in and ask to use the bathroom

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Two single-stall, gendered bathrooms are in a hallway at the back of the store.
comment: Bathrooms (well, at least the men's) have always been clean in my experience.  It's a store, so you might want to buy something, but then again, it's Starbucks.

name: Esso/Tim Hortons
directions: Hallway at the back right.
comment: Not sure about ladies. Mens has an enclosed toilet (walls go floor to ceiling) and locking door.

name: Petro Canada
directions: in the hallway at the back right of the store.
comment: Single locking bathroom. pretty clean. May/2009

name: Ultramar

directions: In the hall at the back. Don't really have to buy anything, it's a gas station.
comment: Unisex single washroom, locking door, pretty clean.

name: Cafe Jack
directions: From the parking lot, enter at the main counter. Bathrooms are to your left.
comment: (213) 365-8882It may be difficult to see this cafe from the street. It looks like a ship.

name: The Dock
directions: In the hallway at the back. ladies room on the left, larger one (not a single) and a second one (single, locking door, accessible). Men's further down the hall on the right.
comment: There are Two ladies rooms, one is a single w/locking door just past the first larger ladies room. In the mens room there are two completely closed in toilets with locking doors (like a bathroom in the bathroom, so noone can see your feet).Bathrooms have awlways been clean when i was there.

name: Pinkberry
directions: Right of the counter, on the far side of the room.

name: Pho 21
directions: Past the counter towards the back dining area.
comment: You will want to ask before using this restroom.(213) 620-0513‎

name: Coffee Been & Tea Leaf
directions: In the hallway, facing the front window.

name: Court House Seafood Restaurant
directions: Bathrooms are in a nook on the right wall of the restaurant, past the drink cooler.  There are two single-seat bathrooms -- women's on the left, men's on the right.
comment: It's a restaurant, so you probably should buy something.  They have excellent seafood!

name: Rochambeau Library
directions: Basement. Take stairs down to the right from the entrance (or elevator to the left).
comment: Monday & Thursday 1:00 pm - 9:00 pmTuesday & Wednesday 9:30 am - 6:00 pm Friday & Saturday 12:00 - 6:00 pmSunday Closed

name: Target (Spectrum Mall)
directions: Front of store, between the two entrances, right at the front of the restroom hallway (before you get to the traditional restrooms)
comment: Clean, \"family\" bathroom (complete with diaper station), no stalls, locking door. This is a new store, so I don't know if most other Target locations have a similar facility, but it is worth a shot.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Along the back wall of the store, about midway, near the traditional restrooms but on a different wall (where Layaway used to be)
comment: Usually fairly clean, it's a \"family\" restroom (complete with diaper changer), no stall, locking door. I have noted that most Wal-Mart locations now have such a restroom.

name: officemax
directions: Located in the diplomat mall right next to biglots
comment: Don't even go in that place its fucken gross there's piss and shit  everywhere. The customer service suckes and half the employees R queer if I were u I wouldn't even go in there.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Starbucks is on the corner of Stuart and Dartmouth. Bathroom is in the back, next to the door into the shared hallway of the building.
comment: You should probably buy a coffee or something, but I've used it when I really need to pee before catching a train (the bathrooms at Back Bay are disgusting, and also gendered) without buying anything and not had a problem.

name: Sobey's
directions: New public access toilets.  Two single-stall lockable rooms in the back of the store near the dairy section. Changing table too.

name: Brideview Bank Building
directions: Safe and secure in Uptown Chicago!See the security guard at the elevators for a key.  They are VERY VERY trans friendly.Plus, if you need a coffee, there's a Starbuck's right there.
comment: 7 days per week 8:00am-9:00pm

name: The Jane Bond
comment: The 2 bathrooms are numbered, not gendered!

name: Method Coffee Bar and Tea Lounge

name: Himalayan Bistro

name: ASU Engineering Center G-Wing
directions: This bathroom is located on the third floor of the building, directly behind the elevators.
comment: Bathrooms investigated by genderWHAT?! and the LGBTQ Coalition at ASU: AIt is clean, well lit, locking and handicapped accessible.

name: ASU Memorial Union
directions: Bathroom is located on the first floor, behind Coldstone. It is between two gender-divisive bathrooms.
comment: Bathrooms investigated by genderWHAT?! and the LGBTQ Coalition at ASU: B+It is well lit, clean, locking, and handicap accessible.  It did not receive an A because of the general shabbiness of the room itself, and because our experience has not always been so pleasant at this location.  Says one coalition member, Òthe bathroom is still creepy, but now well lit.Ó

name: Walgreens

name: Caffe Vita

name: Unicorn Crepes
directions: By the ordering counter. Solitary unisex bathroom which requires a key, designated customers-only.
comment: Not only is it gender-neutral, it is one of the most fabulous bathrooms in Seattle. Words really can't describe it. I'm not sure it's entirely accessible, however. Although it is customers-only, it's well worth it to stop by and try these fabulous Japanese crepes... and get a free milk tea from an automated machine.
